    "Radar systemsAs an active sensing device, the primary task of radar is target detection and parameter estimation.",
    "As shown in Figure 2, the radar transmits a probing signal and receives the echo reflected from the target.",
    "By analyzing the echo, the radar receiver can detect the target and determine its critical information such as distance, speed, and azimuth/elevation angles.",
    "Although there are different radar systems, such as pulsed radar and continuous wave radar, the basic principles are similar.",
    "In the following, we take the multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) pulsed radar system as an example to illustrate its basic principle [83].Consider an MIMO pulsed radar system with N t transmit antennas and N r receive antennas, arranged in a uniform linear array (ULA)."
